              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "For reaction with three emitted particles it is",
                "sufficient to detect two particles (e.g. one neutron",
                "and one proton) at defined positions, the energy and",
                "momentum of the third particle can be calculated from",
                "kinematics. Therefore it is necessary to fix relative",
                "angular position of two detectors using polar angle of",
                "both detectors and their relative azimuthal angle.",
                "The star condition is fulfilled for specific neutron",
                "energy."
              ]
            }
          ],
